hterm_pref_character_map_overrides.message:
This is specified as an object. It is a sparse array, where each property is the character set code and the value is an object that is a sparse array itself. In that sparse array, each property is the received character and the value is the displayed character.

For example:
 {"0":{"+":"\u2192",",":"\u2190","-":"\u2191",".":"\u2193", "0":"\u2588"}}
